AUDIO: 'keeping the reward signal meaningful. It has two main tricks. So, the first one is called isotemporal grouping, which makes sure comparisons are fairer by grouping rollouts at same sampled time step. The second method is called'

[06:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'temporal gradient rectification, which basically helps stop training from being distorted. Now, if you compare this to another alignment method called Flow GRPO fast, you can see that Flash GRPO, which is the blue line, is able to learn'

[06:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
